originalText.text: Please DO NOT park here or at any Icon Parking or Manhattan Parking Group location! When I parked here the car elevator broke and they didn't get a mechanic out to fix it for two days. I had over $650 in expenses to pay for a place to stay and transportation around the city. The workers there assured me that everything would be reimbursed - and I have signed documentation on this. It's been over 3 weeks and still no sign of reimbursement and now the company has stopped responding to my emails. I am looking into legal action against them now.

originalText.text: I left my car here August 12, 2020 and Clorox wipes, Lysol wipes, and Purell were stollen from my trunk. When I got to my friend’s house and immediately realized, I called in telling them items had been missing from my car and got hung up on twice. I told them I’d be returning to the lot to speak to someone when I arrived they had put the gate down so I wouldn’t be able to enter (it was around 7:30 p.m. they don’t close til 11:00 p.m.) I went around to enter through the exit and when I did there was one man there who said “Were you the person that called? Read the sign, are you crazy?” (The sign stated they aren’t held liable for missing items.) I immediately called the police and filed a report, by the end the man came up to one of the officers helping me and stated “what is her name and email, my manager is going to look at the videos.” I was nice to all of the workers at this facility, tipped them, and they did not even drive my car out if the parking spot at the end of my time. I knew something felt off and I hope that this gets investigated and that this person gets fired because they are most likely doing this to everyone’s car that comes in, do not risk your items and go to this lot next time you’re in the area, they will be rude to you, look through your car and steal your belongings.
